    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="bpl.00011.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">328 Mickle Street <lb/> Camden New Jersey</name>
                    <date when="1887-05-25">May 25 '87</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Thanks &amp; God bless you my dear Sylvester Baxter for your kind project for
                me—(whether it comes to a fulfilment or not)<ptr target="bpl.00011_n1"/>—</p>
            <p>—I am feeling pretty well as I write—Should most gratefully accept &amp;
                most intensely enjoy a little spot of my own to live in 6 or 8 months of the 12 in
                country air, so pined for by me—As it is I cannot go to a hotel,— nor
                visiting either—although I have many &amp; kindest invitations—I want a
                cheap ¼ or ½ acre &amp; 4-or-5-room house, spot &amp; design selected by
                myself—</p>
            <p>—If convenient let Sloane Kennedy<ptr target="n3039"/> &amp; Dr Bartol<ptr target="bpl.00011_n2"/> read this—&amp; God bless you all—</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>Walt Whitman</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="bpl.00011.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
